<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="312" pageId="12" pageNumber="311" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1127,219,1556]" lastBlockId="13.[113,1089,219,436]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="312" pageId="12" pageNumber="311">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,402,1435,1459]" pageId="12" pageNumber="311">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Černý, 2011" authorityName="Černý" authorityYear="2011" box="[409,688,1437,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="311" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kerkinica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[409,688,1437,1460]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="311">Melanagromyza kerkinica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[695,778,1436,1459]" pageId="12" pageNumber="311" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is characterized by the presence of reclinate orbital setulae arranged in one row and fronto-orbital plates characteristically projecting above eye in profile. It is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hendel, 1923" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1923" box="[710,1012,1499,1524]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="311" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pubescens">
<emphasis box="[710,732,1501,1524]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="311">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[747,857,1501,1524]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="311">pubescens</emphasis>
